    "spell": {
        "name": "Fearful Feast",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "text": "You open your mouth wide and inhale sharply; you draw in the bravery, self-confidence, and hope to which the frightened target clings and then strip away the target\u2019s false assumption that these fragile emotions can save them from the oblivion of terror. You deal 6d4 mental damage to the creature, which must attempt a Will saving throw.",
